---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About the Owner - Ryan Penny"
	description="Learn about Ryan Penny, founder of Disaster911.net"
	pubDate={new Date('November 09 2025')}
	heroImage="/blog-placeholder-about.jpg"
>
	<section>
		<h2>Ryan Penny - Founder & Owner</h2>

		<p>
			Welcome to Disaster911.net. I'm Ryan Penny, and I created this platform to provide
			critical information and resources for emergency preparedness and disaster response.
			With a passion for helping communities stay safe and prepared, I've dedicated myself
			to building a comprehensive resource that empowers individuals and organizations to
			respond effectively when disaster strikes.
		</p>

		<h3>Mission & Vision</h3>
		<p>
			Disaster911.net was born from the belief that preparedness saves lives. In an
			increasingly unpredictable world, having access to reliable, up-to-date information
			about emergency response can make the difference between chaos and coordinated action.
			My mission is to provide practical, actionable guidance that helps people protect
			themselves, their families, and their communities.
		</p>

		<h3>What Disaster911.net Offers</h3>
		<p>
			This platform serves as a comprehensive hub for:
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Emergency Preparedness Guides</strong> - Step-by-step instructions for preparing for various disaster scenarios</li>
			<li><strong>Response Protocols</strong> - Clear guidance on what to do when disaster strikes</li>
			<li><strong>Resource Directory</strong> - Connections to emergency services, relief organizations, and support networks</li>
			<li><strong>Latest Updates</strong> - Current information on disaster response best practices and emerging threats</li>
			<li><strong>Community Support</strong> - A platform for sharing experiences and building resilient communities</li>
		</ul>

		<h3>My Commitment</h3>
		<p>
			I am committed to maintaining Disaster911.net as a trusted, reliable source of
			emergency preparedness information. Every piece of content is carefully researched
			and regularly updated to reflect the latest guidance from emergency management
			professionals and disaster response experts.
		</p>

		<p>
			Whether you're an individual looking to prepare your family for emergencies, a
			community leader seeking to build resilience, or an organization developing response
			protocols, Disaster911.net is here to support you with the information and resources
			you need.
		</p>

		<h3>Get In Touch</h3>
		<p>
			I believe in the power of community and collaboration. If you have questions,
			suggestions, or would like to contribute to Disaster911.net, I'd love to hear from you.
			Together, we can build safer, more prepared communities.
		</p>

		<p>
			<em>Stay prepared. Stay safe. Stay informed.</em>
		</p>

		<p>
			<strong>- Ryan Penny</strong><br />
			Founder, Disaster911.net
		</p>
	</section>

	<style>
		section {
			margin-top: 2rem;
		}

		h2 {
			color: rgb(var(--accent));
			margin-bottom: 1rem;
			border-bottom: 2px solid rgb(var(--accent));
			padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
		}

		h3 {
			color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
			margin-top: 2rem;
			margin-bottom: 1rem;
		}

		ul {
			margin: 1rem 0;
			padding-left: 2rem;
		}

		li {
			margin: 0.5rem 0;
			line-height: 1.6;
		}

		strong {
			color: rgb(var(--black));
		}

		em {
			display: block;
			text-align: center;
			font-size: 1.1rem;
			margin: 2rem 0;
			color: rgb(var(--accent));
		}

		p {
			line-height: 1.8;
			margin-bottom: 1rem;
		}
	</style>
</Layout>
